records.addlTxt:
GUILTY plea entered to the charge of theft-business setting.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) spend fifteen (15) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court;
2) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination (fulltime in Summer and part time during school);
3) complete sixty (60) hours of community service;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
Minutes.
